	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just got this song too and it can be great, your first problem is a good skill in wind isn't enough, that is what a 50 or so, i don't remember but i would play your invis song while afk for a few hours to max out your wind. At a maxed wind you will play it way more often then you miss a note. Second the odds of you charming and holding charm are based on your charisma so some cha gear will help, with 150 cha i rarely get resists on evens.  that and the best way to engage your pet on something is run by another mob that will attack you on sight, your pet will automatically defend you and everytime you recharm the pet it will go right back to killing the last thing it was attacking. I would suggest you do play and learn this song for it can be a fast way to lvl, at least it has for me. There are a lot more subtle things to making this technique of soloing work too but it would take too long and bore everyone if i were to explain them. Go have fun with it i know i did and i hope this helps some.  BTW i know 150 cha is a bit higher than most might have if they are wearing all the cha gear they own but a pair of +7 cha bracers can be bought for 35-40pp and might be worth the investment.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
