	   <tr><td colspan=2>you've got 5-6k,  well, here is what I did with my bard.  First I went to sol b and I got him all the bronze armor I could for free.  That's just to start him off, I got him bladed thulian claws, does about 10 damage per hit at 19 delay, excellent to kill newbie things.  Get's you to about lvl 14 very quickly.  Then you want to change to something with more damage, I got my bard dual ykesha's.  <br><br>After that I looked up auctions for Singing Steel, whatever you can get, get it, Singing steel is well worth the price.  It has the highest AC for bards, and if you want to twink him good, that is what I would go for.  Now if you have Velious I would go to the orc camps and get Whatever peices of Ry'Gorr you can, that would have to be the second best next to planar armor AC wise.  And lambent.  Try to get rid of your Bronze early on though but it is good to have if you can't afford anything else.  I think all in all I used about 7-10k on my bard.<br><br>For jewelry get velium fire emerald rings, or plat rings, it is 5 ac 55 hp or 6 ac 65 hp.  Remember one thing though I can tell you what to get and it could be a very long post, but remember this for twinking bards you want to go with AC and HP items.  AC always comes first.  Then HP.  Stats don't matter too much stats come secondary.  If you do this your bard twink can be a tank, and a damned good one.  My bard has more AC and HP then most WARRIORS his level.  <br><br>That is all.  <br>&nbsp;<br>Damaddil&lt;Arias'tama&gt;<br>54 Illusionist<br><br>Rizen&lt;Arias'tama&gt;<br>28 Bard<br><br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
